one_reviews_text: We have an Annual Plan $ and we can't look at our own model even if in the Annual Plan description it says that we can use Sketchup Viewer VR

Even the demo model doesn't work properly. Can't do anything without a rather expensive subscription. Sketchup used to support it's home users, but is becoming more corporate orientated and leaving behind a lot of users.
Best option I have found is vrsketch. Look in the sketchup extension warehouse.
This is the best showcase of what you should avoid in VR. Have to login just to try the solution, UI not adapted for 3D space, clunky controls ... actually I can't make a list of all the issues.

review_title: Only works with expensive pro abo!
one_reviews_text: You need a pro abo to view your own models, free is just to view 2 demo models in the program.
